data.title: University of Tulsa Athletics
data.meta_description: Karsen Aguirre (5) Midfielder - TULSA: A three-year letterwinner … has started in 47 out of 53 games … has two goals and seven assists for 11 career points. ...
data.text:
TULSA: A three-year letterwinner … has started in 47 out of 53 games … has two goals and seven assists for 11 career points.

JUNIOR (2023): Started in all 18 games …. helped post shutouts over UTEP, Central Arkansas, UTSA, SMU, and Temple ... picked up an assist against Temple … attempted 18 shots.

SOPHOMORE (2022): Started in 14 of 17 games … ranked eighth in The American in assists (4) … tallied a goal at Missouri State … picked up assists at Mid-America Christian, Kansas City, UCF and Memphis … attempted 29 shots … was named TU’s “Player of the Match” against Creighton and Oklahoma.

FRESHMAN (2021): Started in 14 of 17 games … scored a goal against Central Arkansas … recorded assists against Missouri State and Kansas City … attempted 18 shots.

PRIOR TO TULSA: Played club soccer for the Dallas Texans DA/ECNL, FC Dallas, Solar and Sting soccer clubs … was a three-year letterwinner at Plano West High School … scored 10 goals and tallied 16 assists for 36 points at PWHS … was a three-time all-district honoree … earned all-state honors as a junior … helped PWHS finish as the 2019 bi-district champions.

PERSONAL: An organizational studies major ... born October 18, 2002 … daughter of Richard and Robin Aguirre.
